Base.Explanation: Copy a variable from the session variable list. Both the name and value of the variable are copied. If the variable already exists in the project variable list, the value is overwritten.

ArrayElement.Name: Variable name
ArrayElement.Description: The name of the variable to be copied from the session variable list to the project variable list (example: %ConnectionString%).

Base.Explanation: Create an object in Active Directory. The object is created in a Active Directory domain, organizational unit or other container. Optionally, you can specify the domain controller on which the object is created.

ArrayElement.Name: Domain
ArrayElement.Description: The name of the domain (DNS or NETBIOS style, e.g. tools4ever.com or TOOLS4EVER) where the object will be created. Optionally you can specify the property 'Organizational Unit-Container'. If you specify a value for this property, do not specify a value for property 'LDAP-container' since this specification takes precedence.

ArrayElement.Name: Organizational Unit-Container
ArrayElement.Description: The name of the Organizational Unit-Container where the object must be created (example: Students or Students\Group1). If you specify a value for this property, you should also specify a value for the 'Domain' property. If you specify a value for this property, do not specify a value for property 'LDAP-container' since that specification overrules this specification.

ArrayElement.Name: LDAP Container
ArrayElement.Description: The LDAP name of the organizational unit or container where the object must be created (example: cn=Users, dc=Tools4ever, dc=Com). You must specify either a value for this property or values for the properties 'Domain' and 'Organizational Unit-Container'. If values for both methods are specified, this method takes precedence.

ArrayElement.Name: Domain (controller)
ArrayElement.Description: Optional: The name of the domain controller or domain, used to access to the domain, container or organizational unit where the object must be created. If this value is not specified or the name of a domain is specified, the application creates the account on a domain controller that is to be determined by Active Directory (serverless binding). If a domain controller is specified, the account is explicitly created on the specified controller (server binding). In both cases, Active Directory will replicate the account information to all domain controllers in the Active Directory forests and domains.

ArrayElement.Name: Class name
ArrayElement.Description: The type of the object to be created. Specify as the LDAP class name. Examples: user, contact, group.

ArrayElement.Name: Common Name
ArrayElement.Description: The 'CommonName' corresponds with the 'Common Name' of the new Active Directory object. This name defines the contact in an Organizational Unit and must be unique. You can use property 'Name generation algorithm' to make the name unique automatically.

ArrayElement.Name: Object Distinguished Name
ArrayElement.Description: The Object Distinguished Name of the new object. This property is an 'output only' property and is generated by the application automatically. The 'Object Distinguished Name' is created by the Active Directory automatically when the object is created. Once the object is created, you can store the Object Distinguished Name in a variable (%ODN%) and use the variable in subsequent actions.

ArrayElement.Name: Active Directory Object
ArrayElement.Description: An internal data structure representing the object. This property is an 'output only' property and is generated automatically. This property can be used in other script actions.
